and I start smelling cigarette.

00:01:22.299 --> 00:01:24.540
Heavy cigarette.

00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:27.150
Immediately, in my mind, I'm checked out.

00:01:27.150 --> 00:01:29.499
I'm never going to go to this sushi spot ever
again.

00:01:29.499 --> 00:01:31.459
Now you may say, "Pat, you're judgmental for
doing that."

00:01:31.459 --> 00:01:32.459
Not at all.

00:01:32.459 --> 00:01:33.759
I'm the customer.

00:01:33.759 --> 00:01:34.959
I'm buying.

00:01:34.959 --> 00:01:39.509
I want to go to a place that I buy that I
feel good, and the service is good.

00:01:39.509 --> 00:01:41.819
Now you may say, "Well Pat, how do you know
the service is bad?"

00:01:41.819 --> 00:01:43.740
It's not about how I know the service is bad.

00:01:43.740 --> 00:01:45.399
The mind is an imaginative mind.

00:01:45.399 --> 00:01:47.630
So my mind immediately went to this.

00:01:47.630 --> 00:01:50.829
My mind went to "Ahh, man.

00:01:50.829 --> 00:01:55.700
He probably had a smoke break and he probably
smoked multiple cigarettes because he smells

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:57.380
pretty strong on the cigarette side.

00:01:57.380 --> 00:02:00.609
And, I don't know if he's washed his hands.

00:02:00.609 --> 00:02:03.380
He may or may not have washed his hands.

00:02:03.380 --> 00:02:06.740
And he's going to go out there and carry my
plate and he's going to bring my plate.

00:02:06.740 --> 00:02:08.490
And I'm going to hold it and I'm going to
smell the cigarettes.

00:02:08.490 --> 00:02:09.679
And it's going to bother me.

00:02:09.679 --> 00:02:11.510
I can't eat the sushi.

00:02:11.510 --> 00:02:15.080
So in my mind, we stayed, because nothing
else was open.

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:16.730
